HEADWORD: Dubber
<hw>Dub"ber</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind. <ets>dabbah</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A globular vessel or bottle of leather, used in India to hold ghee,
oil, etc.</def> <altsp>[Also written <asp>dupper</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>M'Culloch.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

